	 <title>System.ToShort</title> 
	 <para></para> 
	 <bridgehead renderas="sect3">Remarks</bridgehead> 
	 <para><symbol>Boolean</symbol>, <symbol>Byte</symbol>,
		  <symbol>Integer</symbol>, <symbol>Long</symbol>, and <symbol>String</symbol>
		  types can be explicitly converted to <symbol>Short</symbol> using this
		  operator.</para> 
	 <para>With a <symbol>Boolean</symbol>, <symbol>true</symbol> will return 1,
		  <symbol>false</symbol> will return 0.</para> 
	 <para>With strings, converts the specified <symbol>String</symbol>
		  representation of a number, with optional sign, to an equivalent signed 16-bit
		  integer.</para> 
	 <para>An error will occur if the value is outside that range of an
		  <symbol>Short</symbol> (-32768 to +32767).</para> 
	 <example> 
		  <title>Example</title> 
		  <programlisting>select ToShort(Integer(1234));
select ToShort("-4567");
select ToShort(false);</programlisting> 
		  <programlisting>1234
-4567
0</programlisting> 
	 </example> 
